content:
Configure AWS Identity and Access Management (IAM) Role for Voice

When using Service Cloud Voice with Partner Telephony from Amazon Connect, you must create a role with the correct policy information. Then, specify the ARN for your IAM role in Amazon Connect.

To create your IAM role:

Log in to your AWS account and select Roles.
Create a role with Account ID 793525387755.
Attach no permissions policies.
Add tags, then click Next: Review.
Enter ProvisioningRole as the Role name exactly as specified.
Click Create role.

After creating the role, add an inline policy from GitHub's SCVProvisioningPolicy.json.
Replace <AWS_ACCOUNT_ID> with your AWS Account ID and skip replacing <BYOAC_CUSTOM_S3_BUCKET> if not applicable.
Name it ProvisioningPolicy.
Copy the Role ARN value to save for future use.

Use the role ARN when setting up Voice in Salesforce.
title: Configuring IAM Role for Service Cloud Voice
